-- Sony Corp. Said to Offer About 30 Billion Yen of Bonds Next Week
-- B y   Y u s u k e   M i y a z a w a
-- 2012-02-28T05:57:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-28/sony-corp-said-to-offer-about-30-billion-yen-of-bonds-next-week.html
Sony Corp. (6758)  plans to sell about 30
billion yen of five- and 10-year bonds next week, according to a
person with direct knowledge of the matter.  The manufacturer told investors it plans to sell about 20
billion yen of five-year notes, and about 10 billion yen of 10-
year debt, said the person, asking not to be identified as the
information is private.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yusuke Miyazawa in Tokyo at 
 ymiyazawa3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
